```mermaid
flowchart TD
    n0[["UserController#findAll()"]]
    n1[["UserService#findAll()"]]
    n0 --> n1
    n2{{"Stream#map(Function) - control flow (traversal)"}}
    n1 --> n2
    n3(["UserRepository#findAll() - external (Spring Data JPA)"])
    n2 -->|"input"| n3
    n4{{"loop stream Stream.map (0..n)"}}
    n2 --> n4
    n5["method ref: this::toResponse"]
    n4 -->|"body"| n5
    n5 --> n6
    subgraph sg0["toResponse"]
        direction LR
        n6[["UserService#toResponse(User)"]]
        n7[["UserResponse#<init>(Long, String, String, Integer, Boolean)"]]
        n6 --> n7
        n8[["User#getId()"]]
        n7 -->|"input"| n8
        n9[["User#getName()"]]
        n7 -->|"input"| n9
        n10[["User#getEmail()"]]
        n7 -->|"input"| n10
        n11[["User#getAge()"]]
        n7 -->|"input"| n11
        n12[["User#getActive()"]]
        n7 -->|"input"| n12
    end
    n6 -->|"next"| n4
    %% Notes:
    %% - Stream, Optional, and common JDK chain operators use a small hardcoded return-shape table; this is not a general type inferencer.
    %% - Optional.orElseThrow return type is flattened to Object; generic-aware unwrapping is intentionally deferred.
    %% - Optional present/empty behavior is rendered structurally, but JFM does not predict which arm runs for a request.
    %% - AOP, @Transactional, @ControllerAdvice, DI qualifiers, and Lombok are not modeled.
```
